Riddle Room
This is a room which is bare on all sides. There is an exit down in the northwest corner of the room. To the east is a great closed door made of stone. Above the stone, the following words are written: "No man shall pass this door without solving this riddle:

  What is tall as a house,
    round as a cup,
      and all the king's horses
        can't draw it up?"
